<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="439" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="44.[1393,2599,1153,1935]" pageId="44" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1395,1749,1704,1737]" pageId="44" pageNumber="439">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. The Perija Small-eared Shrew is currently only known from three specimens: a damaged skull from Colombia collected in 1989, a specimen from Colombia collected in 2006, and a specimen from Venezuela collected in 2009. It has a restricted distribution and seems relatively rare; its ecology is virtually unknown, so additional research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
